          "SAMPLE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "The Cf252 source, about 1/8 in. in diameter, mounted",
                "on 0.003-in. platinum foil and covered with a",
                "100-mu-g/cm2 nickel foil, provided about 10e5",
                "fissions/min for calibration."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "METHOD": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "COINC"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                ""
              ]
            }
          ],
          "DETECTOR": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "SIBAR",
                "TELES"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                "",
                "The fission detectors were p-n junction semiconductor",
                "devices, approximately 1 cm sq and self-collimated,",
                "with each subtending an angle of about 14 degrees at",
                "the center of the chamber. For the fission-fragment",
                "measurements, the cover foils were removed and a lower",
                "level discriminator was set to prevent the natural",
                "decay alpha particles from being counted.",
                "The light charged particles were detected in a deltaE-E",
                "counter telescope consisting of two semiconductor",
                "detectors: a totally depleted deltaE detector, 112 mu-m",
                "thick, followed by an E detector, depleted to depth",
                "of about 400 mu-m. An Al foil with a surface density",
                "of 6.6 mg/cm2 prevented fission fragments and low-",
                "energy electrons from reaching the detectors,",
                "yet transmitted alpha particles with energies greater",
                "than 5.5 MeV. For the alpha-particle measurements, the",
                "counter telescope was covered with 7.6 mg/cm2 of",
                "aluminum to stop fission fragments and alpha particles",
                "from natural decay."
              ]
            }
          ],
